Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Pour the @boiled water{125%ml} into a #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat.

Boil the @Basmati Rice{150%g}, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain, pop back in the #pan{} and cover.

Meanwhile, trim the @Green Beans{80%g}, then cut into thirds.

Heat a #frying pan{} on high heat (no oil).

Once hot, fry the @British Pork Mince{240%g} and green beans, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Break up the mince as it cooks, then drain the fat.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no
> pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, in a #bowl{}, mix together the @Peanut Butter{60%g}, @Sweet Chilli Sauce{64%g},
@Soy Sauce{25%ml} and boiled water (see pantry) until smooth.

Add to the pork mince and simmer, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add a splash of water if it's too thick.

Taste and season with @?salt{} and @?pepper{} if needed.

Share the rice between your #bowls{}.

Top with the satay pork and beans.

Sprinkle over the @Salted Peanuts{25%g}.

Enjoy!